706788f-c.text:
(1)
Shore Road, east side, at and south of 95th Street, showing in the foreground the Richard Bennett house. Portions of this house are alleged to date from the Revolutionary War. It is supposed to have
been struck by a cannon ball in 1776.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, as seen from 95th Street.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, showing a closer view.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Colluction.

706789f-b.text:
(1)  Shore Road, at the S.E. corner oF 95th Street, showing the Bennett homestead, which is also known as the Denyse house. It was owned by the Bennett family from 1857-1873. In 1922 Dr. G.H.V. Hunter was
the owner.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing a building further south.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, as seen from 95th Street.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
